main event: On March 13, 1966, two civilian witnesses reported seeing a bright white, rectangular object at ground level in Artigo, Lone Rock, Wisconsin.
interesting points: The object was described as being about the size of a plum,The observation lasted for approximately 3-5 seconds,The object was observed moving toward the ground in a southeastern direction,No photographs or physical evidence were included with the report,The conclusion drawn by the reporting officer was that the object resembled a meteor.
